1 3. If the court determines that the debt identified by the
2 debtor pursuant to subparagraph (1) of paragraph (a) of
3 subsection 2 constitutes a coerced debt:
4 (a) The court shall order the creditor to immediately cease all
5 collection efforts related to the coerced debt and, if applicable, to
6 take reasonable steps to correct any consumer credit report or
7 similar record to reflect that the debt is a coerced debt;
8 (b) The creditor may join any third party who is or may be
9 liable for the coerced debt or amend its complaint to assert a claim
10 against any such person; and
11 (c) The debtor is entitled to recover from the person who
12 coerced the debtor into incurring the coerced debt reasonable
13 attorney’s fees and costs, but may not recover such fees and costs
14 from the creditor.
15 4. If the debtor believes that providing the information
16 required by subparagraph (3) of paragraph (a) of subsection 2 is
17 likely to result in abuse to the debtor or an immediate family
18 member of the debtor, the debtor may, in lieu of providing the
19 information, submit to the court a statement, signed and sworn to
20 or affirmed by the debtor, that such disclosure is likely to result in
21 abuse to the debtor or an immediate family member of the debtor.
22 5. As used in this section:
23 (a) “Coerced debt” means an unsecured consumer debt or any
24 part thereof incurred for personal, family or household purposes
25 as a result of fraud, duress, intimidation, threat of force or undue
26 influence in the name of a debtor who is a victim of:
27 (1) Sex trafficking as defined in NRS 201.300; or
28 (2) Domestic violence, if the alleged perpetrator is a:
29 (I) Spouse or former spouse of the debtor;
30 (II) Person who has a child in common with the debtor;
31 (III) Person related by blood or marriage to the debtor;
32 (IV) Person who is living with or has lived with the
33 debtor; or
34 (V) Person who was in a dating relationship with the
35 debtor at the time the debt was incurred.
36 (b) “Unsecured consumer debt” does not include a credit
37 instrument, as defined in NRS 463.01467.
38 (c) “Victim” includes a person who alleges that he or she is a
39 victim of an act, regardless of whether or not the alleged
40 perpetrator of the act has been charged with or convicted of the
41 act.
